Coleslaw is the simplest salad to make. The dish is originally from Netherlands. In fact, the name is borrowed from the Dutch expression koosla. Koosla means cabbage salad, because shredded cabbage is the main ingredient. Ingredients; Preparation Step 1 Whisk mayonnaise, sugar, lemon juice, vinegar, pepper and salt together in a bowl until smooth and creamy Step 2 Pour in the grated cabbage and carrots Step 3 (Optional) Refrigerate over night Enjoy with fried chicken or sandwich